Use unconventional data sources to drive innovation; Conduct research and statistical analysis to build and refine the game\u2019s marketplace and game monetization systems by developing relevant metrics and signals; Develop a mechanism to track any sinks and sources through the lifecycle of a player and their virtual items\u2019 interaction in the game to develop correlation models between players and internal economy; Define virtual items and their statistics with the Game Design team and project how each of them modifies the game dynamics; Ensure balancing economy systems in collaboration with the Game Design team and Monetization Manager; Work with Mythical\u2019s Economy Data live data feeds to analyze the potential and actual economic impact of in-game marketplace related changes to assist with identifying opportunities and improvements that will have a positive impact on our game economy; Collaborate with Game Designers and the Marketplace teams to help design and implement features and data metrics to improve user marketplace experience, participation and engagement monetization; Develop and interconnect game workflow data and markets quantitative models to ensure that the game economy is aligned to expected targets; Produce clear, effective design documentation according to project standards and develop an understanding of how to make it effective as possible; Apply and further develop Mythical\u2019s Markets data-driven approach to forecast how players will behave to identify economy bottlenecks and opportunities for improvement. Monitor implementation of economic factors and work closely with relevant teams to ensure that internal economic indicators and drivers remain consistent with the current design; Aim to combine blockchain innovation, data science analytics, and knowledge of existing standards of digital goods to optimize Mythical\u2019s economy system to provide the best experience and monetization opportunities for players Qualifications And Competencies Advanced training in Quantitative Economics, Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Computer Science, Quantitative Finance, Engineering, Data Science or another highly quantitative field (Bachelor\u2019s, Master\u2019s, PhD degree) Understanding of blockchain logic a plus Experience and high proficiency coding in Python, R, C#/C++, Java, and/or JS; Practical experience applying statistical methods to a large amount of data (machine learning knowledge a plus); Deep ML knowledge crucial for developing sophisticated components driving signals and indicators for game progression and economy Strong knowledge of probability and statistics (e.g. machine learning, time-series analysis, pattern recognition, NLP) Experience with SQL/NoSQL databases/datasets(e.g. MongoDB, AWS, Hadoop, etc) a plus Experience with analytical packages (e.g. R, Matlab, SAS) Prior experience working in a data-driven research environment is a plus Independent research experience useful Ability to manage multiple tasks and thrive in a fast-paced team environment Strong work ethic, analytical thinking, intellectual rigor, curiosity and ability to grasp linkages beyond the surface Capacity to work independently and in collaboration with other team members ",
